	<paragraph>				
		<anchor>clusters</anchor>
		<heading>
			<size>2</size>
			<content>Clusters</content>
		</heading>
		<paragraph>
			There are two types of clusters that will be shown when expanding a project node. The icon will either show a cluster (<image>
				<url>../images/cluster/cluster.ico</url>
			</image>) or library cluster (<image>
				<url>../images/cluster/cluster_library.ico</url>
			</image>) based on the set cluster's <link><url>url</url><label>*Library Property</label></link> for the corresponding <link><url>url</url><label>cluster</label></link>.
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph>
			Cluster nodes, like <link><url>url</url><label>*clusters</label></link>, can be nested. Expanding cluster nodes will show subclusters and any <link><url>classes.xml</url><label>classes</label></link> found 
			at that expanded cluster's level.
		</paragraph>

